{"questionId":"21885446","questionHtml":"<p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced></msqrt></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></msqrt></math>.</p>\n<p>Consider the shaded region <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></math> enclosed by the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis and the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>, as shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/e1d2da0cd55df8b5d465d4da755094ad27ab53d2.png\"></p>\n<p>The shaded region <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></math> is rotated by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math> radians about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis to form a solid.</p>\n<p>Show that the volume of the solid is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find an integral involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math> and the square of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone incorrect or absent limits for this <em><strong>M1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msubsup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mi>x</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use integration by substitution&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>u</mi></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>u</mi></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>u</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>0</mn><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msubsup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to integrate by inspection&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>0</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msubsup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone incorrect or absent limits for <em><strong>M1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>The correct limits may be seen or implied by later work for the <strong><em>A1</em></strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find an integral involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math> and the square of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone incorrect or absent limits for this <em><strong>M1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msubsup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use integration by substitution&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>d</mo><mi>u</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msubsup></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong><strong>1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone incorrect or absent limits for <em><strong>M1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>u</mi></math> and <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for both correct limits.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong><strong>G</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21885446","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.6","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The function f is defined as fx=x sin x2, where 0≤x≤π. Consider the shaded region R enclosed by the graph of f, the x-axis and the line x=π2, as shown in the following diagram. The","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"6","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.10—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.16—Integration by substitution, parts and repeated parts","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.17—Areas under curve onto y-axis, volume of revolution (about x and y axes)","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Unit circle definitions of sin, cos, tan. Exact trig ratios, ambiguous case of sine rule"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}